                {
                    "node": {
                        "created_at": "1727932703",
                        "id": "18047961664781316",
                        "text": "Tokyo\u2019s answer to New York\u2019s most iconic sandwich \ud83e\udd6a\n\n\u65e5\u672c\u3067\u6700\u9ad8\u306e\u548c\u725b\u30d1\u30b9\u30c8\u30e9\u30df\u3092\u898b\u3064\u3051\u305f\uff01\n\n@bistronocode is chef @yone_asakusa\u2019s love letter to the food he fell in love with during his tenure at 3-star Michelin restaurants in New York City. Bringing a casual dining spin to refined staples, their lunch menu features insanely good, jazzed-up wagyu burgers.\n\nA hidden gem on their menu is this homemade A4 wagyu beef neck pastrami, packed with 300 grams of flavour. The beef is sourced from Ningyocho Imahan\u2014a long-established, famous butcher in Tokyo. It\u2019s brined, slow-cooked, and smoked with sakura wood for a deep, rich umami.\n\nTopped with house-made sauerkraut infused with caraway seeds, this sandwich might just change the way you see pastrami.\n\n\ud83c\udff7\ufe0f \u00a54345 Homemade Wagyu Pastrami Burger Double (300g)\n\n\ud83d\udccd NY BISTRO by NO CODE (Japan, \u3012100-6590 Tokyo, Chiyoda City, Marunouchi, 1 Chome\u22125\u22121, Shin-Marunouchi Building 7F)\n\n#PR #wagyu #pastrami #tokyoeats #\u6771\u4eac\u30b0\u30eb\u30e1"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
